writer_two:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "Story written, it is time to take it to The Pulp Writer, and receive judgement."
        "[Show your article to The Pulp Writer] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 1):
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inMap false
            add_stat actions -1
            set_button button_writer_two false
            run transition_black writer_door
            clear_dialog
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump game_map

    "The Pulp Writer's door. It's still here. Hopefully she is too. Why wouldn't she be?"
    if (roll writer_two_dead_nightmare nightmare 60):
        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>She's a transvestite, just like you.</span>"
        clear_dialog
        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>Sometimes you people just stop existing. Gone, like a bubble in the mud. *Pop*.</span>"
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "A chill tickles your cheek. A hair blows into your mouth. Blegh."
        "[Knock on the door]":
            play sound doorknock
            "There's a cough, somewhere inside. It echoes through the apartment and escapes through the letterbox."
            play sound dooropen
            run transition_instant writer_door_open
            play music meloncholy
            "A moment later the door opens just a touch, still chained to its latch. Inside you can make out a swaying figure, and a dull grey eye."
    clear_dialog
    play music writer
    talk writer talk "Oh. It's you."
    clear_dialog
    "She coughs."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Well, salut or whatever, Ghost."
    clear_dialog
    "It's The Pulp Writer, but not The Pulp Writer you know."
    "Normally she smells of tobacco and nicotine. She still does, but there's a whiff of mint within her musk today."
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "She's chain smoking oestradiol cigarettes in an attempt to reach the fabled 'oestradiol high'."
    choice:
        talk orb talk "She has reached it, valiantly gone over the top, and been shredded by the machine guns on the other side, which in this metaphor represent the 'depressant' side effect of oestradiol abuse."
        "\\"Bon jaw!\\" [Do a gay little wave] \\"I have my work!\\" [Show her your work] \\"I worked really hard on it a-\\" [Get cut off by the Pulp Writer asking you if you want to come in and talk to her while she does drugs]":
            talk writer talk "Want to come inside and talk to me while I do drugs?"
            clear_dialog
            talk nasty talk "AWOOOOOO! FINALLY!"
            if (roll writer_two_trust_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She trusts you enough not to bother checking your work. That's your bosses' job."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Et alors?"    
                "\\"Y-yes?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Ahah. Bon or whatever."
    complete_objective writer writerTwo
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "She takes the article out of your hand and wanders into her apartment, swaying clumsily with each step."
        "[Follow her]":
            clear_dialog
            play sound doorclose
            run transition writer_apartment_both
            clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "She is so fucked right now, goodness."
    talk nasty talk "Why aren't *we* getting that fucked, she's having a great time!"
    if (roll writer_two_great_lovely lovely 20):
        talk lovely talk "No she isn't."
    "The Pulp Writer slumps on her sofa, it's a miserable thing, ragged, worn, old. The sofa has seen better days too."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Come. Sit."
    play sound clothing
    run transition writer_sofa
    clear_dialog
    "Yesterday she veered erratically from angry to clinically bored. Today is different. There is a sense that her soul has been deflated. Her grey fur is no longer just the colour of her fur, it is her."
    if (roll writer_two_ennui_lovely lovely 60):
        talk lovely talk "The Frankish call this <span class='writtenText'>'ennui'</span>."
        if (roll writer_two_ennui_orb orb 40):
            talk orb talk "Ennui just means sad and bored, it's not the poetic state of being you Anglian's think it is."
            if (roll writer_two_ennui_nasty nasty 20):
                talk nasty talk "Tsk tsk. Orb, have you no soul? Ennui is far more than being <span class='writtenText'>'sad and bored'</span>! 'Tis a state of utter depersonalisation."
                clear_dialog
                talk nasty talk "No more do you feel <span class='writtenText'>'sad or bored'</span> you feel naught. There is nothing for you to feel sad and bored about, and there is nothing to make you stop feeling that way."
                talk nasty talk "To experience ennui is to shatter your being into oblivion and put it back together piece by boring piece as the clock ticks away, until at last, eventually, you are you again."
                clear_dialog
                talk lovely talk "Y-yes, what she said."
                clear_dialog
                talk orb talk "Ennui means you're sad and bored."
            else:
                wait 1000
        else:
            wait 1000
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "The Pulp Writer takes a big drag of oestrodil, and looks at you. She squints, as if your face is one of those 3D magic eye pictures."
    if (roll writer_two_face_nightmare nightmare 20):
        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>May as well be.</span>"
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "She keeps squinting. She's forgotten how time works. Her self conscious nature is, for now at least, numbed. She sinks against you, ever so slightly."
        "[Wave at her] \\"Hello!\\"":
            talk writer talk "I'm fond of you, Ghost. Something about you make me... how you say? Smile? It's odd. *You're* odd."
            if (roll writer_two_like_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She doesn't quite get why she enjoys your company, but it's because you're strange and weirdly peppy in a way she isn't. It's good for her. Adds a bit of a spark to her day. Always she wonders what you'll say next."
            else:
                wait 1000
            if (roll writer_two_like_nasty nasty 20):
                talk nasty talk "She thinks you look fuckable and she's horny. Tired of jacking herself off until she falls asleep."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "She shakes herself out of her haze and looks around, bleary eyed, as if realising where she is for the first time."
    "Her head falls into her hands, she sighs."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Sorry for the mess. I absolutely ruined this place when I went rabid, and never really felt it worth fixing up..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "You didn't really take it in the first time you were here, but it's a tip. The curtains are ragged, as if gnawed and gnawed and gnawed. The wallpaper is scratched as if clawed and clawed and clawed. There's a spattering of blood on the skirting board, as if someone gored and gored and gored..."
        "\\"I think it's nice. Homely. It smells of drugs. Brackets, good, close brackets.\\"":
            "The Pulp Writer snorts, amused by you."
        "\\"It's not that bad here, my cottage had a hole in its roof until very recently, and I've only lived there a few days!\\"" if $data.ghost.roofRepaired:
