        "\\"It's not that bad here, my cottage has a hole in its roof, and I've only lived there a few days!\\"" if (!= $data.ghost.roofRepaired true):
            "The Pulp Writer snorts, amused by you. Then briefly gets very serious."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "You should probably fix that before you... how you say? Catching your death of cold, oui? Still, hole or no, my place is... well..."
        "\\"Damn bitch you live like this?\\"":
            talk writer talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Live'</span>?"
            clear_dialog
            "She looks around vacantly. Shrugs."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Maybe."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "It's a tip. My landlord is going to kill me, but fortunately he never visits."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Regardless, I intend to leave to La República before he has a chance to find out."
        "\\"What's waiting for you in La República?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Freedom. A new start. Communism."
            clear_dialog
            "She coughs into her sleeve."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "The Iberian Republic is the birthplace of modern communism, to the governments of the west it is a miasma spewing corpse attached to Frankreich like a lamprey, but to communists it is the spark of life at the end of the thousand miles of barbed wire."
            clear_dialog
            "She coughs again, worse this time. Wiped her pretty mouth with her ugly sweater sleeve."
            "Catches you looking at her lips. She wants to say something. Is too fucked up. She's so disgusting."
            "Looks away."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "That is why I intend to go to La República, Ghost, because I'm a communist. Only now I have been talking to you I feel perhaps I should stay here, just a little longer. Could it be I am lonely more than I am downtrodden?"
