    clear_dialog
    talk nasty talk "We should just stay here. Let her use us as a bed."
    choice:
        talk lovely talk "Indeed, 'Tis awfully rude to move a sleepy petite dame. Best to leave her where she is and wait for her to wake up."
        "[Stay and stroke the scrungly womans hair]":
            "She immediately starts to drool on you. Hot girl shit."
            clear_dialog
            if (roll writer_two_drool_orb orb 40):
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "She drooled all over your dress too. Sorry. Or not sorry. You probably find that sexy for some fucking reason."
                    "I do.":
                        talk nasty talk "Damn right. Good take, Ghost."
                    "Eh.":
                        talk nasty talk "*I* find it sexy, and I'm the protagonist, right. This is Nasty Girl RPG, right? Right?"
                        talk lovely talk "What on Earth are you blathering about, Nasty Girl?"
                        talk nasty talk "I don't fucking know. Fuck you."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "You don't fall asleep. Instead you relax. It's easier to relax when there's a lady using you as a bed, or from another perspective, with you using a lady as a blanket."
    clear_dialog
    wait 4000
    "It's a while before The Pulp Writer begins to stir. She sniffles. She grumbles. She wiggles about."
    if (roll writer_two_livid_lovely lovely 20):
        talk lovely talk "If she realised you were seeing her like this she would be livid."
        clear_dialog
    "Her nose scrunches. Her ears twitch. Her eyes widen in terror; she has noticed you, but she doesn't have the energy to peel herself off you just yet."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Wh- what happened?"
        "\\"You fell asleep on me.\\"":
            "She squints. She struggles to believe she let her guard down like that."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Hmm."
        "\\"You fell asleep on me, it was really cute actually.\\""     
            "Her pale face turns red."
            if (roll writer_two_bury_lovely lovely 40):
                set this.data.writer.two_neckSnap true
                talk lovely talk "She's weighing her options. Ignore her embarrassment, or snap your neck and bury you in the woods."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "I need a smoke."
            if $data.writer.two_neckSnap:
                talk lovely talk "You got lucky."
    clear_dialog
    play sound clothing
    "The Pulp Writer reaches behind the back of the sofa cushions and pulls out a cigarette tin."
    if (roll writer_two_stored_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "She keeps cigarettes stored in strategic locations around her apartment, she is never more than an arms reach from at least three."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "So."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "She lights her cigarette, and presses it to her mouth. She does not continue speaking."
        "\\"That was nice.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Shut the fuck up."
            clear_dialog
            "Her voice snaps like a branch under a serial killers boot."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Ahem. Mm. Sorry..."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "...It *was* nice. Thank you, Ghost."
    clear_dialog
    "A sniffle, a croak, and then a slight squeeze of her arms around you. She is crying."
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "Sorry Ghost, you're on your own here. I barely even know what crying is."
    talk nasty talk "You and me both. What are you supposed to do when pretty girls cry? I am not emotionally equipped to deal with this."
    talk lovely talk "Tsk. And to think you fancy yourself a séducteur."
    talk nasty talk "How dare. I would never fancy myself anything I couldn't spell."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk lovely talk "Sigh. Ghost, ask her if she's okay, mmm, darling?"
        "\\"Um.\\" [Tap The Pulp Writer's shoulder] \\"Are you okay?\\"":
            talk writer talk "I... Sorry it's just... This... I haven't felt like this in a long time, Ghost... Fuck... Fuck you... Fuck you..."
            clear_dialog
            "She sniffles between her words instead of using full stops."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "I mean thank you. But fuck you also. Godsdammit..."
                "\\"What's wrong?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Everything. Fuck. I've fucked it. I miss them all. The party..."
                "[Stroke her hair]":
                    add data.writer.two_hug 1
                    "She sobs quietly. She's trying really hard to make it inaudible, but she can't."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Everything is fucked. I've fucked it... I miss them all. The party..."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "After it was published that lady, she came up to me on... on. Fuck. I forget..."
                    talk writer talk "But she told me <span class='writtenText'>'You're right, you know? What you wrote about.'</span> and I asked what she meant and she..."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Ah... it was on rue de l'érable, that's it..."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "She pointed upwards, to the black crown above, and she says to me <span class='writtenText'>'it was the boches fault, what happened. It was their shelling'</span> and I cried. That wasn't what it was about, my book. It was about the dominance of the bourgeoisie becoming so unfathomable that it blotted out the sun and rained death on the worker..."
                    talk writer talk "All I had wrote was for nothing..."
                    clear_dialog
                    "Her smoking hand flops off of you, landing inches from her face. She does not flinch from the burning tip. She is enthralled by the glow. By the fire hazard."
                    if (roll writer_two_thorns_ash_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "She's watching her life burn away ash by ash."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
    set data.writer_two.questions 0
    set data.global.writerEiffel true
    jump writer_two_menu

writer_two_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Pulp Writer is sniffling. Half sad, half sickly."
        "\\"The Party?\\"":
            if (!= $data.writer_two.questionParty true):
                set data.writer_two.questionParty true
                add data.writer_two.questions 1
            talk writer talk "My comrades... We met in a local coffee house every week, sometimes more often."
            clear_dialog
            "There's a softness in her voice that feels unnatural coming from her, especially while she's tired and oh so floppy."
            if (roll writer_two_menu_coffee_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She can still smell the coffee beans they used there. A Đại Việt variety. She enjoyed the smell, more so than the taste."
                if (roll writer_two_menu_coffee_orb orb 20):
                    talk orb talk "They don't sell it in Anglia, and even if they did the caffeine would kill her in her current state. Even now she sometimes wonders whether this coffee, plucked unwillingly from Frankish-Indochina, was a hypocrisy of theirs..."
                else:
                    wait 1000
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "I hated those bastards, but I miss them greatly... All gone now. Disagreements in the minutiae of ideology spiralling into squabbling while the secret service laughed."
            talk writer talk "We dreamed of a better world. Of standing side by side with our comrades to build it. And the world killed them all."
            talk writer talk "Perhaps there is no better world? Perhaps there is only the one we have now."
            jump writer_two_menu
        "\\"After what was published? What lady? I'm not really following, sorry.\\"":
            if (!= $data.writer_two.questionLady true):
                set data.writer_two.questionLady true
                add data.writer_two.questions 1
            "The Pulp Writer sighs."
            if (roll writer_two_menu_into_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Do I really want to get into this...'</span>"
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Sous la couronne noire ou : Ciel d'épines'.</span>"
                "\\"Oh! The book you wrote that you hate!\\"":
                    set data.writer.backstory true
                    talk writer talk "Yes... the book I wrote that I hate..."
                    talk writer talk "I did not always hate it. I loved it, once."
                    clear_dialog
                    "Her breathing is shaky."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "You have never been to Pawris, non?"
                        roll writer_two_menu_pawris_orb orb 60 "Have I been to Pawris, Orb?":
                            success "":
                                talk orb talk "No. You once bought a ferry ticket to visit when you were much younger, but were turned away. Chewed on tickets were not considered valid."
                            failure "":
                                talk orb talk "Unsure. Maybe? Let's just say no to be safe."
                    clear_dialog
                    "The question was either rhetorical, or The Pulp Writer's patience short. She does not wait for your response."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "The Eiffel Table, some salaud sought to build a new world atop the old. A shining city in the clouds. The city was rotten, corrupted, diseased. The Eiffel Table was to be an escape."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She spits, realises her face is buried in you, and apologetically laps the spit back up, hoping you don't notice. You do."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "A wrought iron construct, looming over the centre of Pawris, condemning the undercity to shadow. Atop it, buildings, entire streets even. Cafes, book shops, homes, museums..."
                    if (roll writer_two_menu_eiffel_orb orb 40):
                        talk orb talk "The construction of such a monstrosity is as impressive as it was deranged."
                        talk orb talk "The structure is colossal. It looms over a square mile of the city. Four-hundred foot tall. Most Serpent pyramids would quake beneath it in fear. It's only rival on this planet was the city in Siberia, before it was destroyed. A horrendous expense, paid for by increased colonial taxation, increased domestic taxation, and the spoils of the Franko-Qing war."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Of course, it was built by capitalists, and so it was built cheaply by people too overworked and underpayed to care."
                    talk writer talk "A few decades of mismanagement, a brief shelling during The War, and that was it. The entire structure is falling apart. Shedding nuts, bolts, beams, entire buildings like dead skin."
                    talk writer talk "They cannot deconstruct it safely, the entire thing is a single load bearing structure."
                    clear_dialog  
                    talk writer talk "This is the topic of <span class='writtenText'>'La couronne noire'</span>. The sky blocked out by the bourgeoisie's bloodthirsty distaste for the under classes. The workers literally dammed to a lower role in society. A class divide wrought in metal and blood. A tangible reminder of the class struggle suffocating the masses until it crumbles under the weight of its own insanity, kills us all, and kills them with it."
                    if (roll writer_two_thorns_eiffel_orb orb 60):
                        talk orb talk "She watched someone die when a beam fell from the Eiffel Table. It was Chloé. She didn't even like Chloé as a comrade, nor as a friend, still, she was Chloé. Her book was written in this grief."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "The Lady I mentioned, she had read the book, but she did not understand this. It was the Koalition's fault, she said. They shelled it, they killed my friend, that was all."
                    talk writer talk "I asked her why she blamed not those who built it in the first place, and she shrugged."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She sighs."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "Why did I bother writing it? People do not care to have the veil lifted. What was the point."
                        "\\"You really took this one review to heart, huh?\\"":
                            talk writer talk "Perhaps I overreact. Perhaps not. It does not change how I feel."
                        "\\I think I'd understand the message of the book if I read it.\\"":
                            talk writer talk "Maybe you would. Tell me though, would it change you? Would you fight back? Live the revolution? I wrote it, and I did not."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "The workers... we can't arm them, Ghost, their minds have been invaded by propagande bourgeoise... lungs filled with chlore gazeux... they would turn the guns to us, Ghost, to people like us."
                    talk writer talk "To foreigners and refugees and to the people fighting for them... the revolution is betrayed and... oh gods, I feel so sick I might throw up..."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk nasty talk "I stand corrected. Maybe you *can* be a little too high."
            jump writer_two_menu
        "\\"Tell me about the coffee house. I like hearing about things.\\"" if $data.writer_two.questionParty true:
            if (!= $data.writer_two.questionCoffee true):
                set data.writer_two.questionCoffee true
                add data.writer_two.questions 1
            talk writer talk "Ahh... La Haus du Café. That was its name. It was so warm. I think the basement was rented out to a clay worker. Their kiln kept the whole building warm."
            clear_dialog
            "A frown."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "The ventilation down there was not so good. The clay worker often was coughing. Oh well."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "We would sit every time in the same private room. It was slightly too small for us, so we used to take turns having Chloé sit on each of our laps. She was the smallest, yes?"
            talk writer talk "A social democrat... the traitorous bitch..."
            talk writer talk "Anyway... we would sit and talk, argue, till the shop closed. Sometimes till later, if we hid really well."
            if (roll writer_two_menu_hid_orb orb 60):
                talk orb talk "The owner knew they hid, they appreciated the free burglar alarm, and found it funnier not to tell them they could just stay."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump writer_two_menu
        "\\"If they ever build a big iron structure over Bluehills I'll get you an umbrella so you can stay safe if anything falls :)\\" [Say this completely sincerely]" if $data.writer_two.questionLady:
            "The Pulp Writer seems a little confused."
            if (roll writer_two_menu_umbrella_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "She's pretty sure she appreciates it, even if it is a bit of an odd thing to say that doesn't really acknowledge what's upsetting her."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "T- thank you, Ghost."
            jump writer_two_menu
        "\\"I'm sorry you're sad. Here, have a present. It might cheer you up.\\" [Put the Frankish pennies on her head]" if (has_item? pennies):
            remove_item pennies 1
            talk writer talk "Uh... thank you, Ghost."
            if (roll writer_two_menu_pennies_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "It didn't cheer her up. The confusion did briefly distract her from her sadness, though."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "I'll make sure not to spend them all at once..."
            if (roll writer_two_menu_pig_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "She briefly imagined herself as a lemon sheep. She didn't dislike it."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump writer_two_menu
        "[Attempt to cheer her up with a song] \\"~Petite souris petite souris tu as un joli visage, petite souris petite souris tu as un nez~\\"":
            talk writer talk "J'ai un nez? Whatever next..."
            if (roll writer_two_menu_song_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "She enjoyed your song! She thinks you're simple though, I'm sorry to say."
            jump writer_two_menu
        "\\"Sorry I'm asking so many questions when you're sad. I can stop if you like.\\"" if (>= $data.writer_two.questions 3):
            choice:
                talk writer talk "No... no... it's okay. I don't exactly have anyone else to talk to about this... thank you for feigning interest, Ghost."
                "\\"I'm not feigning interest! I'm actually interested!\\"":
                    "She <span class='goldItalic'>smiles</span>."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Okay."
                "[Do a gay ass little salute] \\"That's what Weird Tails best interviewer was hired for.\\"":
                    "She fits a small chuckle in between her sniffles."
            jump writer_two_menu
        "<span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>" if (>= $data.writer_two.questions 3):
            jump writer_two_thorns

writer_two_thorns:
    clear_dialog
    "A grim silence lingers. The Pulp Writer seems finally about to speak, but is interrupted by her hacking cough. It's bad. It's over a minute before she is breathing properly again, and even then her voice sounds like it is passing through a cheese grater."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Merde... je vais mourir... fuck me..."
    clear_dialog
    "She wipes a tear from her eye and sighs. It's a deep sigh, a tired one."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Sometimes I wish they'd never inoculated me. That I'd turned completely. That I'd ceased to be, and was reborn free from all the barbed wire tying me to this pitiful little body and this pitiful little life."
    clear_dialog
    "She peers up into your eyes. They hold contact for far *far* longer than they ever have before. They sparkle, but only with tears. A pair of grey, icy puddles on a winter's morning."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Don't you ever wish that, Ghost? To go sickos? To bite and claw and scuffle and screech in the woods?"
        "\\"All the time. All the time I am wanting to go sickos. I want to grab the world by its fingers and gnaw and gnaw and gnaw till my fur is soaked with blood and they can wriggle no more.\\"":
            add data.writer.two_hug 1
            talk writer talk "And gnaw and gnaw and gnaw... blood... fuck."
            clear_dialog
            "She's become breathy. She liked your answer."
            clear_dialog
            run transition scrungler
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Yes? You want to become scrunkly, Ghost? Become a little scrungler? That is what we call it in Frankish..."
                "\\"We call it that here too. It is a feeling that exists beyond language.\\"":
                    run transition writer_apartment
        "\\"I'm not 100% sure what that means, so I shall be giving a non-committal response. That's wild.\\""
            run skip
        "\\"Nope, not me. I love being a little lady.\\"":
            talk writer talk "I'm glad for you, Ghost."
    clear_dialog
    "She sniffs, a little too late to stop some snot getting acquainted with your dress."  
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "It's cliche, but to endure sentience is to endure suffering, isn't it?"
    clear_dialog
    "She taps some ash away from her smoke. It disappears between a crack in the floorboards. Gone forever."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "What about you, Ghost? I have meandered down l'avenue de whining for long enough alone. What troubles plague *you*?"
        "\\"So um. I don't have any money, and I have to pay rent or I'll like, die, I guess?\\"" if (!= (quest_succeeded? landlady) true):
            talk writer talk "You are asking me to lend you money."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk lovely talk "A statement, not a question."
                "\\"Yes.\\"":
                    "The Pulp Writer exhales some smoke into your face."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "Whatever, I have a little to spare."
                        "\\"Thank you.\\"":
                            talk writer talk "Mhm. Whatever."
                        "\\"Girls rock\\".":
                            "The Pulp Writer's expression does not change. It does not even flinch."
                            clear_dialog
                            talk writer talk "Sure. Girls rock."
                    clear_dialog
                    play sound footstepsinside
                    "She walks over to her desk and scuffles around in the drawer, returning with a wad of money."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "I know it is not much, but maybe it helps, yes?"
                    add_stat money 5
                    play sound coins
                    if (roll writer_two_thorns_corpse_orb orb 60):
                        talk orb talk "She doesn't like having money lying around. It makes her stressed. It feels like having a corpse sat in her apartment."
                        talk orb talk "She's glad it's going to a good home (you), but a little miffed that it will then shortly after go to a bad home (Your Landlady's)."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "\\"No.\\"":
                    "The Pulp Writer exhales some smoke into your face."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Yes you are, but fine, I shan't embarrass you further."
        "\\"I need oestrogen, but I don't know where it comes from. You can see how this is a problem.\\"" if (&& (!= (objective_started? hrt dealer) true) (!= (has_item? hrt) true)):
            talk writer talk "You don't know where it comes from? A lot of it is distilled from oestradiol plants, yes? In Oceania mostly, but sometimes not."
            clear_dialog
            "She clears her throat. It's not a nice sound."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "As for where to get it? I have a lady."
                "\\"You have a lady.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Mhm. A dealer. I get my hormones from her."
                    jump writer_two_dealer_menu
        "\\"Nothing. I am completely content with my life.\\"":
            talk writer talk "I'm quite sure you're not, but I shall not delve."
    jump writer_two_leave

writer_two_dealer_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Pulp Writer looks out the window. She's looking through the amber glow of the city, and into the stars. She cannot see them. Not tonight, but she knows they are there, looking down on her."
        "\\"Tell me about your <span class='writtenText'>'dealer'</span>.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Not much to tell. We aren't friends. She seems nice though. Funny accent, not one you get around here. I don't know Anglia well enough to place it. Northern maybe..."
            jump writer_two_dealer_menu
        "\\"Are moonshine hormones safe?\\"":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "I don't know. Is trusting in a healthcare system that wants you dead to one day help you safe?"
                "\\"I'm not sure. Is it?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "No."
                "\\"Was that a yes?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Well. I'm not dead yet."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She coughs into her elbow."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Not quite..."
            jump writer_two_dealer_menu
        "\\"How much does she charge?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Mmmmm... my memory... it is not so good for numbers..."
            clear_dialog
            "She thinks."
            clear_dialog
            set data.dealer.priceGuessed true
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Thirty or so pounds? I forget exactly."
                "\\"That's expensive.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "For something that should be free with the national healthcare system? Yes."
                    talk writer talk "For something a woman went to the time to gather ingredients for, brew in her bathtub, bottle into vials and then stand out in the cold selling to other transexuals?"
                    clear_dialog
                    "She blows some smoke in your face, for no particular reason."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "It's a fucking steal."
                "\\"A very fair price for the labour I assume goes into brewing moonshine oestradiol. Now *that's* communism.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Mhm. Dios's bendiga la revolución, baby."
                    if (roll writer_two_dealer_menu_communism_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "She's being glib. She's not entirely convinced you know what communism means, but she appreciates your enthusiasm."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
            if (roll writer_two_dealer_menu_price_orb orb 40):
                set data.dealer.priceKnown true
                talk orb talk "She charges thirty-five pounds exactly."
                if $data.global.visitedShop:
                    if (roll writer_two_dealer_menu_stickers_orb orb 80):
                        set data.dealer.stickers true
                        talk orb talk "Though she may also be willing to trade for some of those gold star stickers the shop sells..."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump writer_two_dealer_menu
        "\\"Could you not simply just give me some of your hormones?\\"":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Like a vampire? What?"
                "\\"Well, if you *want*?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Mmm. Maybe. I do not think it works like this though."
                "\\"No no! I mean just, give me them with your hands!\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Oh. I see."
                    if (roll writer_two_dealer_menu_high_nasty nasty 20):
                        talk nasty talk "She's still a bit high."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "No. Sorry. I need to get some of my own. We pay you enough to afford your own, yes?"
                    if (roll writer_two_dealer_menu_funnel_orb orb 40):
                        talk orb talk "Mostly she just doesn't want to admit the first thing she did when she got high was funnel half of her cash to Die Rote Garde in Brenneburg. They need to buy nails and trinitroxypropane so they can get one up on the fascists."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
            jump writer_two_dealer_menu
        "\\"Where can I find this 'dealer'?\\" <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            start_objective hrt dealer
            talk writer talk "She lurks somewhere along lunden road most evenings. I think probably she likes how serene it is out there at night. You can see the city lights in the distance."
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer speaks slowly. She is recalling something she had almost forgotten."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "I sat with her once and watched the streets go dark as the moon rose..."
            clear_dialog
            "She returns to normal."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Give her my regards if you see her, mhm?"
            set data.writer.dealerWriterHi true
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "This is great intel. We should definitely investigate Lunden Road once it gets dark."
            jump writer_two_leave

writer_two_leave:
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Anyhow. I have work to do, and so you had better be off, yes?"
    clear_dialog
    play sound footstepsinside
    run transition writer_apartment
    choice:
        "She starts walking to the door, with the implication that you should follow her. She grabs an envelope, your payment from Weird Tails, on the way."
        "[Follow her]":
            play sound dooropen
            "The Pulp Writer opens the door and motions for you to step outside, which you do."
            play sound coins
            add_stat money 30
            "She passes you the envelope as you cross the threshold. It's cold outside. It's much nicer in her apartment, with her." 
    clear_dialog   
    choice:
        talk writer talk "I'll let soon you know when our dickhead boss has read your work. I'm sure it'll be fine though. Fuck him."
        "\\"Okay.\\" [Nod] \\"Sounds bopper.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Mhm. Right. Bopper. I'm young enough to know what that means."
        "\\"Is he actually called 'Our Dickhead boss'?\\"":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Yes. That's his name."
                "[Shake your head] \\"Holy smokes! Cruel parents!\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Mmm."
                    if (roll writer_two_leave_sarcastic_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "She was being sarcastic."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "\\"That's fair. I mean, I'm called Ghost, so I can't really judge him on that.\\"":
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "Mmm. I like your name. Ghost. It's nice."
                        "[Blush like a little queer]":
                            "She notices your cheeks redden. She <span class='goldItalic'>smiles</span>. Internally."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Well, à bientôt, Ghost."
        "\\"Be an tot to you too.\\" [Walk away]":
            if (> $data.writer.two_hug 3):
                talk writer talk "Ghost."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    "You turn around. The Pulp Writer takes a timid step out of her doorway, and embraces you. It's a tight hug, a comfortable one. Her gangly arms wrap around you with surprising strength. She <span class='goldItalic'>smiles</span> against you."
                    "[Hug her back]":
                        talk writer talk "Thank you. For earlier."
                        clear_dialog
                        "She lets go of you. Her hair rustles in the breeze. She looks down at her cigarette, no more eye contact for today, she's had a week's worth. She sniffs. She's still full of snot, but then, who isn't?"
                        clear_dialog
                        choice:
                            talk writer talk "Maybe we can go for a walk soon. The day after tomorrow maybe? I can walk to your cottage and we can abscond into the woods, yes? No?"
                            "\\"Yes. That sounds nice. I like walking. I do a lot of it actually. I've basically just been walking back and forth across town via increasingly inefficient routes all week.\\"":
                                set data.ending.presentWriter true
                                add data.dream.womenOptions 1
                                talk writer talk "Bon. À plus tard, Fantôme."
            else:
                choice:
                    "The Pulp Writer hovers at her door for a moment. She's about to close it. This is your chance. Deploy 'Walkies Protocol'."
                    "\\"Um. Um. Before I go, would you like to come for a little walk with me the day after tomorrow?\\"":
                        "The Pulp Writer thinks for a moment. Ponders the thought of a walk."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk writer talk "Very well. Let's. At your cottage, yes? À plus tard, Fantôme."
                        set data.ending.presentWriter true
                        add data.dream.womenOptions 1
            clear_dialog
            play sound doorclose
            if $data.ghost.neckBitten:
                choice:
                    "She shuts the door. The wind is making your ears cold. Your neck still hurts a little. Her bitemark, and her cut, will not disappear for a while."
                    "[Do a gay little smile] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                        play sound spendAction
                        start_objective writer pride
                        jump goToGameMap
            else:
                choice:
                    "She shuts the door. The wind is making your ears cold."
                    "[Shiver] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
